OL,3,CIndia swelters in record-breaking 50C
OL,4,Cheatwave
OL,6,FThe country's weather department
OL,7,Fexpects temperatures to stay high
OL,8,Facross the region for the next few
OL,9,Fdays and has put several states on
OL,10,Fhigh alert.
OL,12,FIt said heatwave conditions will
OL,13,Fcontinue in Delhi on Wednesday but are
OL,14,Fexpected to subside starting Thursday.
OL,16,FApril, May and June are hot in most
OL,17,Fparts of India before monsoon rains
OL,18,Fbring cooler temperatures, but warm
OL,19,Fweather has been getting more intense
OL,20,Facross the past decade.
